com.datascience.cascading.scheme

Class CsvScheme

  • java.lang.Object
    • cascading.scheme.Scheme<org.apache.hadoop.mapred.JobConf,org.apache.hadoop.mapred.RecordReader,org.apache.hadoop.mapred.OutputCollector,Object[],Object[]>
      • com.datascience.cascading.scheme.CsvScheme
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Traceable, Serializable

    public class CsvScheme
extends Scheme<org.apache.hadoop.mapred.JobConf,org.apache.hadoop.mapred.RecordReader,org.apache.hadoop.mapred.OutputCollector,Object[],Object[]>
    The CSV scheme provides support for parsing and formatting CSV files using Apache Commons CSV.

    This scheme is designed for use a source or a sink in a Hadoop MR2 flow.

    To use the scheme, simply construct a new instance, passing either the Fields or a CSVFormat defining the structure of the CSV file. 

       CSVFormat format = CSVFormat.newFormat(',')
       .withHeader("user_id", "first_name", "last_name")
       .withSkipHeaderRecord(true);
     CsvScheme scheme = new CsvScheme(format);
     Tap tap = new Hfs(scheme, "hdfs://users.csv");

    The CSV scheme changes its behavior according to the Fields or CSVFormat provided to the constructor. In cases where fields or columns are not directly specified in the configuration, the scheme may be able to detect the field names from the CSV header. See specific constructors for more information.

    Internally, CsvScheme uses CsvInputFormat and CsvOutputFormat for sourcing and sinking data respectively. These custom Hadoop input/output formats allow the scheme complete control over the encoding, compression, parsing, and formatting of bytes beneath Cascading's abstractions.

    Author:
    Jordan Halterman

    • Constructor Detail

      • CsvScheme

        public CsvScheme()
        Creates a new CSV scheme with CSVFormat.DEFAULT.

        Strict mode is enabled when using this constructor.

        Note that because the default CSVFormat does not specify a header record or skip the header record, this constructor will result in Fields being dynamically generated for sources. Source fields will be generated with positional names, e.g. col1, col2, col3, etc.

      • CsvScheme

        public CsvScheme(boolean strict)
        Creates a new CSV scheme with the CSVFormat.DEFAULT format.

        Note that because the default CSVFormat does not specify a header record or skip the header record, this constructor will result in Fields being dynamically generated for sources. Source fields will be generated with positional names, e.g. col1, col2, col3, etc.

        Parameters:
        strict - Indicates whether to parse records in strict parsing mode. When strict mode is disabled, single record parse errors will be caught and logged.

      • CsvScheme

        public CsvScheme(CSVFormat format)
        Creates a new CSV scheme with the given CSVFormat.

        Strict mode is enabled when using this constructor.

        When used as a source, if CSVFormat.getHeader() is specified, the provided header column names will be used in the output Fields. If no headers are specified and CSVFormat.getSkipHeaderRecord() is true, the scheme will attempt to automatically detect the header record from the first record in the CSV input. If CSVFormat.getSkipHeaderRecord() is false and no header record is provided, positional Fields will be generated, e.g. col1, col2, col3, etc.

        Parameters:
        format - The format with which to parse (source) or format (sink) records.

      • CsvScheme

        public CsvScheme(Fields fields)
        Creates a new CSV scheme with the given source and sink Fields.

        Strict mode is enabled when using this constructor.

        The provided Fields will be used both in sourcing and sinking. For sources, this constructor assumes that the provided number of fields match the number of columns in the source data. For sinks, only columns with the provided field names will be written to the output target.

        Parameters:
        fields - The source and sink fields.

      • CsvScheme

        public CsvScheme(Fields fields,
         CSVFormat format)
        Creates a new CSV scheme with the given source and sink Fields and a custom format with which to read and write CSV data.

        Strict mode is enabled when using this constructor.

        The provided Fields will be used both in sourcing and sinking. For sources, this constructor assumes that the provided number of fields match the number of columns in the source data. For sinks, only columns with the provided field names will be written to the output target.

        Note that regardless of whether the CSVFormat provides a header record, the source Fields take precedence, and the header record configured in the format will be essentially ignored.

        Parameters:
        fields - The source and sink fields.
        format - The format with which to parse (source) or format (sink) records.
